                    <ContentView Padding="40,0,10,20" VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                        <Label x:Name="lbl_Text2" Text="Intended in part for classroom instruction, this app provides teachers with the digital sources and narrative-building tools that will help foster an understanding of the multifaceted topic of World War I. With this app you will be able to create collections in a way that complements your existing resources. And you're free to reuse  all available partner content." FontFamily="TrebuchetMS" TextColor="White" FontSize="20"></Label>
                    </ContentView>

                    <ContentView Padding="40,0,10,20" VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand" x:Name="cv_WhatFor">
                        <Label Text="What can I use the app for?" TextColor="#e0665e" FontSize="20"></Label>
                    </ContentView>

                    <ContentView Padding="40,0,10,20" VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                        <Label Text="The core of what we want the app to do is gather collections together in a way that people can tell stories. Using this app, teachers will be able to create collections using featured WWI films and images, interweaving personalized text to tell the stories of a local training camp or to trace the movements of a regiment. " FontFamily="TrebuchetMS" TextColor="White" FontSize="20"></Label>
                    </ContentView>

                    <ContentView Padding="40,0,10,20" VerticalOptions="StartAndExpand">
                        <Label Text="There are no pre-made activities or lessons within this app—see our DocsTeach resource at the bottom of this page—but we've provided the basic tools for creating collections in a way that highlights the rarely seen WWI content being digitized by the National Archives, and allows you as teachers to formulate relevant historical questions. This focus on the reuse and enrichment of primary sources allows for flexibility in creating new historical narratives." FontFamily="TrebuchetMS" TextColor="White" FontSize="20"></Label>
                    </ContentView>

